o the unknown to do what they think is right. But what if every new discovery hints that the thing they need to be the most careful of is their supposed friend himself?&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="tvtropes"></category><category term="pretender"></category></entry><entry><title>Kanae meets Internet</title><link href="http://specularreflection.github.io/idle/tvt-kbdh-14578.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2014-04-05T00:58:57+00:00</updated><author><name>Specular</name></author><id>tag:specularreflection.github.io,2014-04-05:idle/tvt-kbdh-14578.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;… and viceversa.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="tvtropes"></category><category term="images"></category></entry><entry><title>Get Them With The First Impression.</title><link href="http://specularreflection.github.io/idle/tvt-kbdh-14557.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2014-03-08T06:45:35+00:00</updated><author><name>Specular</name></author><id>tag:specularreflection.github.io,2014-03-08:idle/tvt-kbdh-14557.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Just like that time in the classroom, he said&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="tvtropes"></category><category term="script style"></category></entry><entry><title>Can (Not) Be Too Prepared</title><link href="http://specularreflection.github.io/idle/tvt-kbdh-14362.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2013-10-25T12:09:32+00:00</updated><author><name>Specular</name></author><id>tag:specularreflection.github.io,2013-10-25:idle/tvt-kbdh-14362.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Inspired by a Brick Joke from Chapter 63.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="tvtropes"></category></entry><entry><title>Unspoken</title><link href="http://specularreflection.github.io/idle/tvt-kbdh-14040.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2013-06-28T02:13:33+00:00</updated><author><name>Specular</name></author><id>tag:specularreflection.github.io,2013-06-28:idle/tvt-kbdh-14040.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Just a WAFFy epilogue to