rm="script style"></category></entry><entry><title>Refuge in Audacity</title><link href="http://specularreflection.github.io/idle/tvt-kbdh-13940.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2013-05-30T16:00:30+00:00</updated><author><name>Specular</name></author><id>tag:specularreflection.github.io,2013-05-30:idle/tvt-kbdh-13940.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mostly, I wanted to play around with a classic framing device. Honestly.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="tvtropes"></category></entry><entry><title>Taniguchi's snippet</title><link href="http://specularreflection.github.io/idle/tvt-kbdh-13927.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2013-05-29T04:20:06+00:00</updated><author><name>Specular</name></author><id>tag:specularreflection.github.io,2013-05-29:idle/tvt-kbdh-13927.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Brought to you by the &amp;ldquo;What Did I Do Last Night?&amp;rdquo; trope.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="tvtropes"></category></entry><entry><title>Can't help it.</title><link href="http://specularreflection.github.io/idle/tvt-kbdh-13459.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2013-01-02T20:06:14+00:00</updated><author><name>Specular</name></author><id>tag:specularreflection.github.io,2013-01-02:idle/tvt-kbdh-13459.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;That&amp;rsquo;s why there are clichés in the first place.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="tvtropes"></category><category term="script style"></category></entry></feed>